Congratulations*c* You made it through the first day!\n\nYou'll be scored by how many actions you make.
I hope you're enjoying Social Sessions.\nIf so please leave a rating!
You can take as much time as you need to complete a session.
However if you want 3 stars*c* then you'll have to do it in as few actions as possible.
Use the Restart button to quickly start a session over if you've made a mistake.
Finish all sessions to move to the next day.
If you get stuck*c* feel free to give me a call.\n\nI'll be happy to help.
It's a new week!\n\nLet me see what you can expect this week...
Some groups are special.\n\nWhen you see this symbol there will be one person that you will not be allowed to interact with.
There will be other types of special groups in future weeks as well.
When you see this symbol people will become upset if you do not interact with them quickly enough.
When you see this symbol you won't be able to\nsee how your patients are connected with\none another.
When you see this symbol you will only be allowed to interact with each person one time.
Tip:\n\nSome groups aren't very friendly with each other. Even with a lot of enemies in a group*c* you can still help them...
For example*c* some of these have no friends.
You can still make them happy indirectly...
We'll have to find another way to make them happy...
Luckily there's still someone you can discourage to make him happy.
And finally*c* he has a friend*c* so you can easily make them both happy!
It might help to think of it in a straight line.
Start by discouraging the second to last one...
... it doesn't matter how many enemies there are in a row...
...just keep discouraging one to make the one behind it happy...
...and if you can find a friend eventually...
...then you'll be able to make everyone happy!
So keep an eye out for groups like this that have a line of enemies and then a friend.
Tip:\n\nYour final action must be an encouragement*c* and it must be with someone who only has friends and no enemies.
Sometimes it's helpful to figure out your last action*c* first.
Find someone with only friends for your last action
There has to be at least one*c* or the session would be impossible.
Now*c* you just need to make everyone else happy first.
Then*c* you know that your final action will make him and all of his friends happy
